cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "myGPT — LLM Fundamentals & Advanced Topics: building a GPT-2-level language model from scratch"
abstract: >-
  A 28-chapter code-along tutorial that constructs a GPT-2-style language model
  from scratch in PyTorch. Part I (Chapters 1–18, "LLM Fundamentals") covers
  tokens, attention, the transformer block, training, generation, and a CLI.
  Part II (Chapters 19–28, "Advanced Topics") covers device-aware training,
  bf16 mixed precision, training-loop hardening, byte-pair encoding, RMSNorm,
  RoPE, grouped-query attention, and a real ~500 MB Wikipedia training run.
  Every line of code is introduced and explained.
type: software
